Vintage style illustration of a frustrated person sitting at a cluttered home desk, surrounded by a chaotic tangle of modems, routers, and ethernet cables from the mid-2000s era. The scene features warm sepia and amber tones with a grainy film quality. On the desk sits a boxy beige modem with blinking lights, instruction manuals scattered about, and the person's hand resting on their forehead in exasperation. A window in the background shows a sunset, suggesting hours spent troubleshooting. The composition emphasizes the isolation of dealing with technology alone, cables snaking across the floor like stubborn vines. The aesthetic evokes early internet frustration with aged photograph coloring and subtle vignette edges.
